&lt;p&gt;FP&amp;amp;A spans the full spectrum of the Company’s activities, focusing on financial analysis, planning, analytics and decision support. Operational reporting and data engineering development are not within FP&amp;amp;A&#39;s scope. Where specialist expertise is needed, FP&amp;amp;A engages appropriate functions rather than executing the work directly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior FP&amp;amp;A Analyst is a key contributor within the Group FP&amp;amp;A function, supporting the development and delivery of high-quality management reporting and performance analysis across the organisation. The role focuses on producing accurate, insightful and forward-looking analysis that helps enhance the quality and usefulness of financial information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior FP&amp;amp;A Analyst will support the implementation of analysis that incorporates trends, leading indicators and forward-looking insight. While the role will not lead formal budgeting or forecasting processes, it will contribute analytical input and performance insight through management reporting, scenario analysis and trend-based assessment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is primarily focused on Revenue and Cost of Sales analysis, supporting understanding of performance drivers, margin development and overall profitability at Group and Vertical level. Working closely with the current Senior FP&amp;amp;A Analyst and the wider finance team, the Senior FP&amp;amp;A Analyst will contribute to reporting improvements, analytical initiatives and continuous improvement activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Accountabilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare regular management reporting and performance analysis focused on Revenue, Cost of Sales and overall profitability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development and enhancement of group-level reporting frameworks, metrics and analytical outputs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the review and improvement of existing reporting, identifying opportunities to enhance insight, efficiency and forward-looking value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide input on feasibility and effort required for new analytical requests, supporting realistic scoping and prioritisation of FP&amp;amp;A work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform trend analysis and incorporate leading indicators into reporting outputs to support a more forward-looking view of performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyse financial performance to identify trends, variances and areas requiring further investigation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide analytical support to Finance Business Partners and senior finance stakeholders through accurate data and reporting, liaising with other teams where support is required.&lt;/li&gt;
